    summary: "Janet Mui, Head of Market Analysis at RBC Brewin Dolphin, discussed the recent pullback in semiconductor stocks, characterizing it as a healthy consolidation following a strong rally rather than the beginning of a broad market reversal. She emphasized that the fundamental demand for semiconductors continues to far outstrip supply, supporting ongoing investor interest. Despite occasional market…",
    body: "Janet Mui, Head of Market Analysis at RBC Brewin Dolphin, discussed the recent pullback in semiconductor stocks, characterizing it as a healthy consolidation following a strong rally rather than the beginning of a broad market reversal. She emphasized that the fundamental demand for semiconductors continues to far outstrip supply, supporting ongoing investor interest. Despite occasional market jitters triggered by news events, such as developments in the cloud computing sector, Mui highlighted that the underlying fundamentals remain robust.\n\nThis strength has led to a rebound in chip stocks after the recent US holiday, with investors taking advantage of price dips during consolidation phases. (Source: Bloomberg)",
